## Policy Decisions

- Use per‑jail ipset sets for clarity and control.
- Default action is `DROP` via iptables for matched banned IPs.
- All manual bans/unbans go through Fail2Ban:
  - Ban: `fail2ban-client set <jail> banip <ip>`
  - Unban: `fail2ban-client set <jail> unbanip <ip>`
  - Never add/remove IPs directly in `iptables`; let Fail2Ban manage ipset.

